eNCA's Barry Bateman reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have made another breakthrough into a kidnapping syndicate operating in Lenasia. The Anti-Kidnapping Task Team has arrested the brother of the alleged mastermind. WATCH | Crime in SA | Kidnapping on the rise They've also seized cash at a house suspected of being used to hold hostages. Last month the Anti-Kidnapping Task Team arrested Faizal Charloos, the alleged kidnapping kingpin, and mastermind behind several high-profile hostage cases. Hundreds of thousands of rand were seized at his home.